<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row" id="reviewAndBiasContainer">
    <div class="col-md-5" id="reviewPopup">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="cityName col-sm-10">
          <% city = City.last %>
          <%= city.name %>
        </div>
        <div class="cityScore col-sm-2">
          <div class="cityCircle" style="background-color: #<%= city.color_gradient %>">
              <div class="cityScore"><%= number_to_percentage(city.city_review_average * 10, precision: 0) %></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviewContent">
        <div class="reviewTitle"> Tobias K.'s Take</div>
        You’ll come to Siem Reap for Angkor Wat, which is breathtaking, but the city is a nice little bonus. Charming and walkable there’s plenty of delicious food choices and places for a drink. It can get pretty rowdy in parts, but overall it’s a great value ($.50 beers!) and much more pleasant than I expected.
        <div class="row seeBiasButton">
          <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3"><button>See Tobias's Bias</button></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3" id="biasCard">
      This is the bias card which is three columns
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="map"></div>
<script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=AIzaSyBT-cR8W-TCwZLqfIIDgASK9Tl-wAMHay8"></script>


